@startuml C4_L4_Availability
title C4 Level 4 — High Availability & Health-Check Chain\n(ASR-AVAIL-01, ASR-PERF-01)

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #003366
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #DDEEFF
    ParticipantBorderColor #336699
    LifeLineBackgroundColor #EEF4FF
    LifeLineBorderColor #336699
    NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
    NoteBorderColor #F9A825
    FontName Arial
}

participant "Internet\nClient" as C #A8D8EA
participant "Caddy :443\n(lb_policy first\nhealth_uri /api/health\nhealth_interval 10s)" as Caddy #95CAA0
participant "backend-primary\n:8000\n(Node.js 20)" as BP #DDEEFF
participant "backend-secondary\n:8000\n(Node.js 20)" as BS #CFE2F3
participant "PostgreSQL 16\n(postgres-data\nvolume)" as PG #C5CAE9
participant "Redis 7" as RD #FFB74D

== Startup Health-Check Chain ==
PG -> PG : pg_isready -U $POSTGRES_USER\nevery 10s [healthcheck]
RD -> RD : redis-cli ping\nevery 10s [healthcheck]
note over BP, BS
  depends_on: db (service_healthy) + redis (service_healthy)
  Both backends start only after DB + Redis pass health checks
end note
BP -> BP : npx prisma db push\n→ node dist/index.js
BP -> BP : GET /api/health → HTTP 200\nevery 10s [healthcheck, 3 retries, 20s start]
BS -> BS : npx prisma db push\n→ node dist/index.js
BS -> BS : GET /api/health → HTTP 200\nevery 10s [healthcheck]

== Steady-State: Primary Serves Traffic ==
C -> Caddy : HTTPS request /api/*
Caddy -> Caddy : encode gzip/zstd\n(ASR-PERF-01: reduce payload)
Caddy -> BP : HTTP /api/*\n[active — lb_policy first]
BP -> PG : Prisma query\n(parameterized)
BP -> RD : rate-limit INCR\n/ cache read
PG --> BP : result
RD --> BP : counter / cache hit
BP --> Caddy : HTTP 200
Caddy --> C : HTTPS 200\n(compressed)

== Failover: Primary Goes Down ==
Caddy -> BP : GET /api/health
BP --> Caddy : [no response / non-200]
note over Caddy
  health_fails 1 → mark backend-primary unhealthy
  health_passes 1 → required to restore
end note
Caddy -> BS : HTTP /api/*\n[promoted to active]
BS -> PG : Prisma query\n(same DB, shared state)
BS -> RD : rate-limit / cache\n(same Redis, cross-instance accurate)
BS --> Caddy : HTTP 200
Caddy --> C : HTTPS 200\n(no visible interruption)

== Recovery: Primary Restored ==
BP -> BP : Docker restart: unless-stopped\nauto-restarts container
BP -> BP : GET /api/health → HTTP 200
Caddy -> BP : health_passes 1 → restored
note over Caddy, BP
  Caddy returns to lb_policy first (primary)
  Zero downtime achieved via passive failover
end note

note over BP, BS
  <b>ASR-AVAIL-01</b>: 99.9% uptime
  Both instances are STATELESS (JWT auth, shared PG+Redis)
  → Any instance can handle any request
  → restart: unless-stopped guards against crash loops

  <b>ASR-PERF-01</b>: < 2s under 500 concurrent users
  Two instances share load; Caddy compresses responses;
  Redis cache avoids expensive DB aggregations
end note
@enduml
